<br>
 Yale was quite correct about it all coming down to mass ratios (as I'd written about earlier).<br>
 Maybe a simpler way to look at it is measuring the required Delta-V for the proposed mission. The maximum speed is ~400km/sec (which is incredible alone), but the total delta-V is above 1600km/sec. Prove that a useful &amp; realistic proposed ship design can do this, and I'll nominate you for the highest award that the AIAA, AAS, NASA, and the Nobel Prize committee can bestow.<br>
 You'll have accomplished a miracle the Vatican itself would have to take notice of.<br>
<br>
